## MESSAGE 2 — Sales Team (Supabase MCP)

This message draws from `mcp__claude_ai_Supabase__execute_sql` against `SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID`.

### Step T1: Schema mental model

- `team_members` — `email`, `full_name`, `is_admin`, `suspended`. **Sales reps** (graded on scoreboard): zoe, jean-marie, mael (ramping new-hire), quang. **Founder-led** (separate section, not on rep scoreboard): ludo (CEO — runs high-touch customer deals + partnerships + investor track). **Founder outbound** (info-only): milstan (founder, automated nurture batches). Milan and Ludo are NOT compared to reps.
- `attio_meetings` — calendar meetings. **`participant_emails` is often empty** — read participants from `raw->'participants'->[]->>'email_address'`. `starts_at` is meeting time. `linked_records` carries CRM links.
- `attio_call_recordings` — `transcript_status='ok'` + `segments>0` means transcript usable.
- `attio_call_transcript_segments` — `meeting_id`, `speaker_name`, `speech`, `start_time`, `end_time`. Long calls (segments > 1500) are usually substantive.
- `emails` — Gmail correspondence. `direction` = inbound/outbound. `team_member_emails` lists which @leadbay.ai accounts are party.

### Step T2a: Milan founder-led automated outbound

`milstan@leadbay.ai` is the founder, not a sales rep. He runs an **automated nurture pipeline** that sends templated emails to engaged customers (recent verified signups, quota hitters, returning users). These are NOT rep-led 1:1 outbound and should NOT count toward the rep leaderboard, but they ARE customer-facing engagement and deserve a dedicated section.

```sql
WITH milan AS (
  SELECT * FROM emails
  WHERE 'milstan@leadbay.ai' = ANY(team_member_emails)
    AND direction = 'outbound'
    AND internal_date >= '{start}' AND internal_date < '{end}'
)
SELECT
  COUNT(*) AS sent,
  COUNT(DISTINCT thread_id) AS threads,
  (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT r) FROM milan, unnest(recipients) r
     WHERE r NOT LIKE '%@leadbay.ai') AS distinct_external_recipients
FROM milan;
```

Then list subjects + recipients to identify:
- **Automated batch fingerprint** — many emails sent within seconds of each other with templated subjects ("Quick check-in", "votre setup", "wishlist Leadbay") targeting different recipients = automated nurture run.
- **Manual founder outreach** — investor/partner emails (Transpose VC, etc.) and bespoke customer threads (multi-recipient HomeSpirit follow-up).

Render as a dedicated `🤖 MILAN AUTOMATED OUTBOUND` section: total sent, distinct recipients, batch date, top customer targets that overlap with this week's quota-hitters or verified-signups (cross-reference Message 1). Exclude investor replies (e.g., `*.vc` recipients) — those belong to the fundraise track, not sales.

### Step T2: Per-rep meeting + email totals

```sql
WITH mp AS (
  SELECT m.meeting_id, m.title, m.starts_at,
         ARRAY(SELECT jsonb_array_elements(m.raw->'participants')->>'email_address') AS emails
  FROM attio_meetings m
  WHERE m.starts_at >= '{start}' AND m.starts_at < '{end}'
)
SELECT t.email, COUNT(*) AS total,
  COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM unnest(emails) e WHERE e NOT LIKE '%@leadbay.ai' AND e <> '')) AS external
FROM mp
JOIN (VALUES ('quang@leadbay.ai'),('jean-marie@leadbay.ai'),('zoe@leadbay.ai'),('mael@leadbay.ai')) t(email)
  ON t.email = ANY(mp.emails)
GROUP BY t.email;
```

Then list every external meeting per rep (title + external attendee emails) — needed for Step T3.

```sql
SELECT t.email, COUNT(*) AS sent FROM emails e
JOIN (VALUES ('quang@leadbay.ai'),('jean-marie@leadbay.ai'),('zoe@leadbay.ai'),('mael@leadbay.ai')) t(email)
  ON t.email = ANY(e.team_member_emails) AND e.direction = 'outbound'
WHERE e.internal_date >= '{start}' AND e.internal_date < '{end}'
GROUP BY t.email;
```

### Step T3: Classify Ludo's external meetings (CRITICAL)

Ludo is the CEO/boss — **not on the rep scoreboard**. His customer activity is **founder-led sales** and gets its own dedicated `👑 Founder-led sales` section in Message 2, similar in spirit to Milan's `🤖 Founder outbound` block (but for high-touch real conversations, not automated email).

His calendar also mixes **investor**, **partner/program**, **press**, **financing/bank**, and personal meetings. Filter aggressively: only **real customer** meetings show up under Founder-led sales.

**Investor / fundraising signals:**
- Domain ends in `.vc` or `.fund`
- Known angel networks: `coreangels.com`, `ycombinator.com`, `entrepreneurfirst.com`, `transposeplatform.vc`
- Title contains "intro", "fundraising", "VC", "fund", "residency"
- Fund/angel-sounding personal Gmail addresses participating in 1:1s with Ludo

**Partner / program / legal / service-provider / financing signals:**
- Cold-call cup, startup contest, "residency", legal counsel (`*law*`, `*nmlaw*`, `*conseil*` in legal context)
- Known partner orgs (Swish, Indy, h-7.eu, Rennes-SB cold-call event, Deel Pitch sponsorship event)
- Known service providers / agencies: `bulldozer-collective.com` (+ `lmgiudicenti@gmail.com`)
- Sales-coaching / GTM webinars (`salescraft.fr`, `salesconversionpartners.com`, `richconsulting-group.com`, `elriclegloire.com`)
- Press / network (`maddyness.fr`, `frenchtechjournal.com`, `cfnews.net`, `ccmbenchmark.com` (JDN), `frenchfounders.com`)
- Peer-tooling networks (`atrios.com`, `heypastel.com`, `ziphq.com`, `klark.ai`, `firstdegree.io`, `earleads.com`, `runploy.com`, `acquisitionandconsulting.com`)
- **Banks / financing for Leadbay** (NOT customers — they're giving Leadbay loans/financing): `lcl.fr` (Crédit Lyonnais, see `aurelien.mercier@lcl.fr` on May 12 loan signature). If notable, surface as a small "📌 Outside sales — company milestone" footnote, not a customer win.
- Internal-product-style "weekly sync" with non-customer accounts

**When unsure:** mark as ambiguous → exclude from customer count, don't list under top wins. Optionally surface in a one-line "ambiguous" note in GAPS so the user can correct.

For Quang, Zoé, Jean-Marie: assume external = customer unless title/domain clearly says otherwise (e.g., personal-Gmail lunch with a friend, partner program). Same investor/partner filter applies if it lights up.

**Do not** include investor or partner meetings in the leaderboard, wins, or actions. They are out of scope for sales retro.

### Step T4: Pull notable transcripts (privacy-respecting)

For each call with `transcript_status='ok'` and `segments > 1500`, pull the transcript and derive insights **without ever quoting verbatim**.

**NEVER expose "segments" in the output.** That's an Attio internal data-model term — sales people don't know what it means. Translate it into sales-native language:

- **Duration in minutes** — sum `(end_time - start_time)` across segments → real call length. Sales people book in minutes.
- **Stakeholder count** — count distinct customer-side `speaker_name`. "1:1" / "small (2–3)" / "buyer team (4+)" / "exec room (6+)".
- **Stage label** — infer from meeting title + recurrence + participant mix:
  - **discovery** — first call, single contact, generic title ("Meet X", "Quick chat")
  - **demo / pitch** — "Présentation", "Demo", multi-DM first-time room
  - **multi-DM pitch** — buyer team or exec room, presentation-shape
  - **deep-dive** — long, technical title ("Data architecture", "Mise à plat", "Validation Intégration")
  - **negotiation** — pricing / commercial / contract titles, recurring contact
  - **save / debrief** — "Debrief / next steps", "Catch up", post-incident
  - **kickoff / onboarding** — "Onboarding", "Kickoff", new admin in attendance
  - **follow-up** — "Suivi", recurring weekly with same contact
- **Heat tier** — based on quota hits + recurrence + stakeholder count: 🔥 hot / 🔶 warm / cool. Don't emit cool calls in TOP WINS.

**Allowed derived insight (privacy-safe):**
- Topic clustering ("Product/feature questions dominated; pricing came up briefly")
- Outcome inference ("Next-step booked" / "Objection raised" / "Champion identified")
- Sentiment shape ("Warmer in second half" / "Skeptical opening, engaged finish")
- Risk flags ("Champion is leaving the company" / "Procurement deadline mentioned")
- Counts (decision-makers in room, distinct objections, follow-up commitments)
- Talk-time ratio ("rep-led ~63%" / "balanced") — derived from speaker_name aggregation

**NOT allowed:**
- Verbatim quotes from any speaker
- Names of internal stakeholders the customer mentioned but who are not Leadbay employees
- Specific numbers (revenue, headcount, salary) the customer disclosed
- Personal details (health, family, opinions about other vendors by name)

```sql
SELECT speaker_name, speech, start_time
FROM attio_call_transcript_segments
WHERE meeting_id = '{uuid}'
ORDER BY segment_index;
```

If you can't derive a useful privacy-safe insight, skip the call. Better to omit than to leak.

